This application is intended for production deployment (static hosting, CDN, reverse proxy, and/or Kubernetes for the UI asset server).

## Deployment posture
- Prefer boring, well-supported deployment patterns (static files behind a CDN or reverse proxy, or a minimal container image serving static assets).
- Keep infrastructure and pipeline configuration explicit, reviewable, and reversible.
- Do not rely on preview-only platform features unless explicitly required.

## Static assets and caching
- Set cache headers intentionally for hashed assets vs. `index.html` (immutable long cache for hashed bundles; short or no cache for `index.html`).
- Avoid serving stale app shells that reference removed chunks after deploys.

## Containers (when used)
- Use a minimal base image appropriate for static serving (e.g. nginx or distroless).
- Run as non-root where supported.
- Pin image and dependency versions in manifests; do not use `:latest` in production.
- Keep secrets out of plain manifests and source code.

## Configuration
- Keep environment-specific configuration externalized (build-time public env, runtime injection).
- Separate public config from secrets; never bake secrets into client bundles.
- Do not hardcode environment-specific API base URLs without a clear build/deploy strategy.

## Networking and traffic
- Terminate TLS at the edge; enforce HTTPS redirects in production.
- Keep health and readiness meaningful if the UI is served from a Kubernetes workload (respond when the static server can serve traffic).

## Observability
- Prefer client-side RUM and error reporting integrated with backend trace correlation where available.
- Do not ship verbose debug logging to production users by default.
